HEADWORD: Breastsummer
<hw>Breast"sum`mer</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>A summer or girder extending across a building flush with, and
supporting, the upper part of a front or external wall; a long lintel; a
girder; -- used principally above shop windows.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>brestsummer</asp> and <asp>bressummer</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Breastwheel</ent>⟦br⟧
